text:
$AAPL Monthly Discount Range 👀

We’re testing the monthly market bias again. The last six times $AAPL hit this level, institutions stepped in hard and pushed the stock to new highs.

I was a buyer at $170 two months ago.

But now I’m sitting out until we get at least one full month of higher lows on the BX Trender.

Breaking the market bias is extremely rare. The only times we’ve seen that happen for any real length were in 2016, 2013, and during the 2008 crash.

If you’re bullish on Apple, history says this is a solid zone to accumulate. But for me, I’m staying patient and waiting for confirmation.
